-- 
De Vere Group CEO, Financial Officer to Leave, Times Reports

-- B y   K i t   C h e l l e l
-- 
2011-09-17T11:27:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-17/de-vere-group-ceo-financial-officer-to-leave-times-reports.html
De Vere Group Plc, the U.K. hotel
company which owns the Grand Hotel in Brighton, is preparing to
announce the departure of its chief executive officer and chief
financial officer, the London-based  Times  reported.  De Vere CEO Richard Balfour-Lynn will be replaced by
chairman Andrew Coppel in changes to be announced next week, the
newspaper said, without saying where it got the information. The
company’s CFO Jag Singh will also depart, the Times said.  Telephone calls by Bloomberg News to De Vere’s headquarters
in Warrington northern-England and its public relations company
Fleet Street Consulting were not answered outside normal working
hours today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kit Chellel in London 
